# 🛡️ Lab 03 – Traffic Analysis Exercise (You Dirty Rat)

## 👨‍💻 Overview
This lab is part of my SOC PCAP Analysis Series.  
It focuses on analyzing a real-world malware infection scenario using Wireshark.

The objective was to investigate malicious network traffic and document findings in an incident report.

---

## 🎯 Objectives
- Analyze PCAP traffic using Wireshark
- Identify infected host and user activity
- Extract Indicators of Compromise (IOCs)
- Understand post-infection behavior
- Map activity to MITRE ATT&CK techniques

---

## 📂 Files in this Lab
- report.md → Full incident report
- iocs.txt → Extracted indicators of compromise
- task.md → Original lab instructions
- screenshots/ → Wireshark evidence (optional)

---

## 🧪 Tools Used
- Wireshark
- DNS analysis
- Kerberos protocol inspection
- TLS/HTTPS traffic analysis

---

## 🚀 Outcome
Improved understanding of:
- Active Directory authentication traffic
- Malware command and control patterns
- DNS-based reconnaissance
- SOC investigation workflow
